ChicagoFLF font (Gibbous/Resources/Fonts/ChicagoFLF.ttf)

ChicagoFLF, used to render the System-7 retro skin, is a TrueType revival of
Susan Kare's Chicago typeface (the Macintosh interface font, 1984-1997). It was
created by Robin Casady and released into the public domain, free for personal
and commercial use.

  https://fontlibrary.org/en/font/chicagoflf

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Lunar texture maps (Gibbous/Resources/Textures/Moon.jpg, MoonNormal.jpg)

The lunar albedo map (Moon.jpg) used by the Metal-rendered Moon is from NASA's
CGI Moon Kit, assembled from data collected by the Lunar Reconnaissance Orbiter
camera and laser altimeter instrument teams.

  https://svs.gsfc.nasa.gov/4720/

  Credit: NASA's Scientific Visualization Studio

The normal map (MoonNormal.jpg) is derived from the CGI Moon Kit elevation
(displacement) map using the Normal Map Creator tool.

  https://xo3d.co.uk/tools/normal-map-creator/

